Class BucketSort

  • java.lang.Object
    • BucketSort

  • public class BucketSort
extends java.lang.Object
    BucketSort algorithm as described by Professor Dorin. Written by Edward Bachoura. Takes in a list of doubles through standard in and then returns them in ascending order. Note: I wrote this class with all static methods and therefore there are no fields that are native to the BucketSort class and also no constructor.

      • bucketSort

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> bucketSort(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> listOfDoubles,
                                                               double largestValue,
                                                               double smallestValue)
        Uses a bucketSorting algorithm to sort any given list of doubles in ascending order. Uses multiple private helper methods and help in instantiating the buckets, calculating the bucket index, and sorting the actual buckets.
        Parameters:
        listOfDoubles - A list of doubles in an ArrayList, as recieved from System.in.
        largestValue - The largest value that is contained within the listOfDoubles.
        smallestValue - The smallest value that is contained within the listOfDoubles.
        Returns:
        Returns the original listOfDoubles, but sorted in ascending order.
